                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>At the right side of the entrance into the western <hi rend="italic">gōpura</hi> of the second <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> in Tyāgarājasvāmin temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>[Dēvarāya II]. Ś 1362: 1440 A.D.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This record mentions <hi rend="italic">Mahāprādhāna</hi> Lakkaṇṇa Daṇṇāyaka Uḍaiyar. The details of date given <hi rend="italic">viz.</hi>, Ś. 1362, Raudra, Bhādrapada ba. 1, Monday, Rēvati, regularly correspond to 1440 A.D., September 12, ·48; ·83.</p>						
                            
                            <p>It records the erection of the <hi rend="italic">gōpura</hi> as a service to god Valmīkanātha by Nāgaraśar, son of Siddaraśar, of Vasishṭha <hi rend="italic">gōtra</hi> and Āśvalāyana <hi rend="italic">sūtra</hi>, for the merit of Lakkaṇṇa-Daṇṇāyaka.</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
